Enabling GPU in my project still has been a mystery. I couldn't get the delegate working but you can always look for enabling at the android side. You can refer to the NNAPI implementation in the class file attached below. <denchmark-link:https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/files/3496271/TFLiteObjectDetectionAPIModel_javaClass.txt>TFLiteObjectDetectionAPIModel_javaClass.txt</denchmark-link>

		For anyone who hasn't resolved the issue, this is how i resolved the issue;
I noticed that the output tensor of the sample detection model is different from the output tensor of my custom model so i tweaked the TFLiteModelObjectDetectionAPIModel.java file by changing the numBytesPerChannel, NUM_DETECTIONS, variable to match mine.
PS: IF you don't know your output tensors, you can check it with this wonderful too > <denchmark-link:https://lutzroeder.github.io/netron/>https://lutzroeder.github.io/netron/</denchmark-link>

